column5: Hey Guys been a Lurker for a while, Great site. Anyways I'am looking for a private cottage for two people on Lake Nip or the BOQ. For the week starting June 20,09. Prefer a private cottage to a resort, haven't had a alot of luck searching the net, and it's geting a bit late. Any help would be much appreciated. Thought I'd add a pic of my biggest small stream speck of the year a real beauty for the size of streams I fish. Cheers ldub http://i168.photobucket.com/albums/u161/ld.../Picture597.jpg
Try cottagelink.com, you should be able to find something there.
Try this as a third option.  lots of bass walleye and pike.  i had a blast here.  Good luck  http://www.cottagesunlimited.com/cottpages/cott181b.htm  or even use this site to find a place
Nipissing all the way for a near north experience. Check here.... www.getnorth.ca.
Have a looksee for BOQ  www.quintefishing.com/cottagerentals.htm
nippissing cottage.  I have stayed here before and am heading up for a week june 1. If you have a boat its a great cottage on an island. lots of pike and walleye in the area.
Nipissing certainly has it over BOQ for scenery and I've never been at a loss to get fish, there's plenty.
A cousin of mine owns that place. It is in a very nice spot. Well kept cottage and they will look after you.
Thanks for the reply's definitely going to go with Nipissing, the BOQ is great and good fishing but there is just something about nipissing. thanks again ldub
Thats good, i have nothing but good things to say about the place, the owners are great fishing is great and i love lake nippissing.
Try Nanmar Cottages just West of Callander Bay. I'll be up there from June 11 to 14, can't wait...
